I ordered $40 worth of takeout for my family. I typically order the spicy tuna roll but last time I ordered it was a little too spicy so this time I ordered the mild tuna. Once my order arrived, I noticed that the mild tuna just consisted of huge chunks of raw tuna and seaweed wrap. I called immediately and apologized, explaining that I made a mistake thinking this roll was the same as the spicy tuna but milder. The woman who answered the phone stated I got the wrong order and I could come pick up the mild tuna roll. I thanked her and confirmed all the ingredients I typically get in the spicy tuna roll. She placed me on hold and then another woman got on the phone stating that there was no mistake and what I received was a mild tuna roll. I explained the situation again and she said there was nothing they could do for me. I understand that I ordered the wrong roll but the customer service was harsh. There was no attempt to accommodate me in any way. Honestly, this hasn’t been my first experience with this type of customer service at Kofusion but because of the quality of the food, I always return. Not anymore, this was very disappointing.

excellent sushi.  howeve they need a menu detailing what you are eating when it arrives to the table especially on 1.00 sushi nights.  also a take home menu would be great and inexpensive to produce.
Great night out with my boy for some incredible sushi.  Our server was super friendly and on top of everything.  Looking forward to another visit.

The atmosphere was nice and they have really good sushi--the taste and presentation showed quality and I liked the little details like piped wasabi and a basket for the edamame.  Kevin, our server, had impeccable timing and his crème brûlée was perfect. Definitely coming back!

The food is always amazing.  The sushi is terrific and so is the stir fry with udon noodles.  But does anyone else think that the little figures in the fish tanks look a little like a certain part of the male anatomy?

Food is fresh and amazingly delicious!  Started off with crab cakes and they are the best I've ever had!  Light and full of crab and flavor!  I had the Halibut.  AMAZING!  My wife had beef stir fry and it was so tender!  Highly recommend!  Table service was top notch!
Very nice sushi and the miso is tasty
Love the food and the atmosphere!
For starters pork dumplings and coconut shrimp. Chicago roll, Volcano roll and Flaming Phoenix. GONE FAST!
My daughter has taken me there twice. Both times were amazing. Only recommendation is different drinks to choose from..
Great food!

Overpriced appetizers cannot be overstated. Ordered the dumplings, and for $8 I expected more than 4 dumplings. They were undercooked and not at all the correct texture. Sushi was just okay, didn't taste particularly fresh, and all of their custom rolls are loaded with sauces presumably to mask the subpar fish they use. One thing there isn't a lack of is the overly-attentive waitstaff. They will visit your table to the point of being simply bothersome.  I am confused as to how this location can operate and taste so different than the campus location, which is much, much better. We won't be returning to the downtown location.
I try to order different sushi each time I go and it's delicious every time. Always look forward to coming back!
